  "text": "The following is a more detailed description of the HSI process used in this study, adopted from Gillies et al. [CITATION_1] Raw sample images (S) and reference images (R) were smoothed using a three-point mean filter along spectral dimension of the image cubes. The smoothed sample image cubes (S) were ratioed against the smoothed reference image cubes (R) to convert the data to an optical density scale (A). The optical density at pixel i,j (Aij) of each raw image was calculated by:",
